<br>
My question as stated above.<br>
<br>
My knowledge of SG:<br>
I have tried SG two times so far. Both of the time, my groups consisted (myslef-58 warrior , 57 chanter, 56 rog, 52 druid, 52 wizzy and 52 cleric) lesser succor across to the safe point. Then walk around in the tunnel to its exit with 2 Gold Fishes Statues, then camp at the right hand side. Pulled whatever we see.<br>
<br>
From there, I could see a Well with 2 mobs guarding.<br>
<br>
I know the WC is dropped from a water elemental like mob called Shimmering Sea Spirit. It is said it spawns in the CASTLE.<br>
<br>
My questions are:<br>
<br>
Where is this CASTLE located? How do I get there based on my knowledge of SG?<br>
<br>
Is my grp strong enough to get ourselves to the Castle camp, hold it and kill the Spirit?<br>
<br>
Any valuable advice?<br>
<br>
In my server, uber weapons are either Overpriced, e.g 80k for SboZ or Not being sold at all. So, I would like to camp this uber WC myself if possible!<br>
<br>
Many thanks in advance.<br>
   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 12:41:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to camp Wavecrusher in SG?</span><hr size=1> As I understand it, the shimmering sea spirit can spawn any place a icy elemental or watery elemental can spawn.  There are two places I know of that have a fair number of these spawn that you can camp.<br>
<br>
One is down the well you've noticed.  That well is actually a tube you can go down with mobs in it.  You can go under the rim of the tube and pop up in a room.  In this room are a number of siren spawns, a couple molktor spawn, and about 6 elemental spawn points.<br>
<br>
Another spot is coming in from the CS zone.   If you go into the water, follow the right wall past an opening into another section of the zone.  At that point hug the left all and surface, looking for a spot you can jump out of the water.  There is a small platform that has a ramp going up from it.  This ramp leads to a bridge, going right onto the bridge leads into a 'castle tower' with a number of sirens/molktor/elemental spawns.  Pretty tough area to break, be sure to bring an enchanter and a very solid group.  Maybe two enchanters.<br>
<br>
The shimmering sea spirit is a rare spawn and the wavecrasher is his rare drop.  I camped the first spot in two sessions for a total of about 12 hours to get mine. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A> at: 7/30/02 3:49:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrutultarewmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 647<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 2:31:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to camp Wavecrusher in SG?</span><hr size=1> The castle is really tough to break, better have a monk and an enchanter at the very least.  I have pulled some ungodly trains trying to do that as a warrior and never had much luck.  The well on the other hand, is relatively easy to break into, and once you make it down, it's pretty much easy single pulls.  The sirens drop tons of breastplate gems, and there's quite a few elementals.  Keep in mind that the elementals have a pretty nasty AE, but they are sub-55 and can be chain-stunned by a paladin/cleric/enchanter and that will keep them from AEing.<br>
<br>
The only hard part of the well is getting down the tube.  Sometimes sirens will aggro you through the tube, and there's a fairly tough mermaid at the bottom of the tube (sometimes two) that are pretty buggy about coming up the tube if you try to pull them.  Once you're down there, it's nice easy exp and pretty good drops, besides a chance at a wavercrasher. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>

