<a href=http://www.realpoor.com>Tarew Marr</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujustfive.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Just Five</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 261<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 3:18:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to camp Wavecrusher in SG?</span><hr size=1> My group and I camped in SG for alittle while.  If you are near the WW zone area, you can &quot;hear&quot; the Shimmering &quot;casting&quot;.  Drove me crazy.  Called in another group of friends because we'd never been into SG deep.<br>
<br>
We pulled the swordfish from the &quot;well&quot; by jumping in the water next to the ledge looking at the Castle.  They see invis so it's important to get rid of them.<br>
<br>
Then we invised up and swam straight down the well.  Hang a left at the bottom and you swim up into a small alcove area with a few elementals and sirens.  The shimmering was the spawn on the left side of the ledge when we came out of the water.  We set up around it and the enchanter targeted the sirens for mez's.  Broke invis and killed Shimmering, looted WC, chanter kept everything mez'd (about 3 mobs since we stayed tight in that small area) and we ported directly out via the druid.<br>
<br>
We had camped the Big Castle (near the CS zone area) a few times prior but never saw the Shimmering.  Being able to &quot;hear&quot; it casting was what gave us the lead to be able to find it.<br>
